  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "With the release of [v0.9](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1453) to facilitate new shading proposal. This PR tracks to the progress to align Prysm to v.0.9 which is important for multi client test net. The experimental branch for this is: https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/pull/3760\r\n\r\nThe v.0.9 consists of the following:\r\n## Beacon chain\r\n### feature\r\n\r\n- [x] alter beacon proposer selection logic (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1413)\r\n- [x] add seed domains (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1415)\r\n- [x] fix delay-based attestation inclusion reward (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1434)\r\n- [x] use eth1_block_hash for initial randao_mix (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1447)\r\n\r\n### simplifications\r\n\r\n- [x] remove active active_index_roots and compact_committees_roots from phase 0 (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1329)\r\n- [x] remove shards/crosslinks from phase 0 (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1428)\r\n- [x] remove transfers from phase 0 (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1443)\r\n\r\n##  Fork choice\r\n\r\n- [x] verify state root in fork choice tests and other minor fixes (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1454)\r\n\r\n\r\n##  Validator\r\n\r\n- [ ] add simple attestation aggregation strategy (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1440)\r\n- [x] remove validator API and migrate to eth2 APIs repo (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1366)\r\n\r\n##  Networking\r\n\r\n- [ ] add simple attestation aggregation strategy (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1440)\r\n\r\n\r\n##  Simple Serialize\r\n\r\n- [x] define summaries and expansions (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1360)\r\n- [x] add clarifications on deserialization (https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1381)\r\n- [x] update to v0.9 version of the spec in the go-ssz repo\r\n\r\n##  Spec test\r\n\r\n- [x] slot processing\r\n- [x] block processing\r\n- [x] epoch processing\r\n- [x] proto compatibility\r\n- [x] ssz\r\n\r\n##  Run time\r\n\r\n- [x] one node with 64 validators\r\n- [x] two nodes with 128 validators each",
